        <item>
            <title>K Kwong：我唔想食纸   「纸餐具多有害化学物质、比想像污糟」</title>
            <link>https://unwire.hk/2024/04/25/paper-is-dirty-said-by-k-kwong/life-tech/green-2/?utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=paper-is-dirty-said-by-k-kwong</link>
            <comments>https://unwire.hk/2024/04/25/paper-is-dirty-said-by-k-kwong/life-tech/green-2/#respond</comments>
            <dc:creator>
                <![CDATA[Oscar]]>
            </dc:creator>
            <pubDate>Thu, 25 Apr 2024 07:20:01 +0000</pubDate>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[环保]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[纸餐具]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[走塑]]>
            </category>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">https://unwire.hk/?p=1231232</guid>
            <description>
                <![CDATA[<p>首阶段即弃胶餐具和塑胶产品管制已于本月 22 日正式实施，行政长官李家超早前表示「走塑」对市民影响不大（<a href="https://unwire.hk/2024/04/23/john-lee-said-no-plastic-doesnot-affect-citizen/life-tech/green-2/">相关报道</a>），但前化学科补习导师「Dr. K. Kwong」就表示，纸餐具除了不环保外，更比想像中「污糟」。</p><p>K Kwong 表示部份纸有 polychlorinated dibenzo-p-dioxins （PCDDs）、polychlorinated dibenzofurans （PCDFs）、polychlorinated biphenyls（PCBs），并分享了不少外国研究结果，大部份均表示纸杯含有有毒化学物质，而且与塑胶杯相比，纸杯并没有更加环保。研究显示，纸杯具有耐水耐热的 PFAS 化学物质，会污染承载的饮料。</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1231233" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439432924_9631613585-445x580.jpg" alt="" width="445" height="580" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439432924_9631613585-445x580.jpg 445w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439432924_9631613585.jpg 584w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 445px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲图片来源：<a href="https://www.facebook.com/DrKKwongChem/posts/963307448490314">K Kwong@Facebook</a></p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1231234" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439456305_9631613851-441x580.jpg" alt="" width="441" height="580" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439456305_9631613851-441x580.jpg 441w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439456305_9631613851.jpg 684w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 441px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲图片来源：<a href="https://www.facebook.com/DrKKwongChem/posts/963307448490314">K Kwong@Facebook</a><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1231235" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439438046_9631614085-451x580.jpg" alt="" width="451" height="580" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439438046_9631614085-451x580.jpg 451w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439438046_9631614085.jpg 700w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 451px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲图片来源：<a href="https://www.facebook.com/DrKKwongChem/posts/963307448490314">K Kwong@Facebook</a><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1231236" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439482340_9631613751-694x468.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="468" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439482340_9631613751-694x468.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439482340_9631613751.jpg 1254w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲图片来源：<a href="https://www.facebook.com/DrKKwongChem/posts/963307448490314">K Kwong@Facebook</a><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1231237" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439586213_9631614185-359x580.jpg" alt="" width="359" height="580" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439586213_9631614185-359x580.jpg 359w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/439586213_9631614185.jpg 557w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 359px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲图片来源：<a href="https://www.facebook.com/DrKKwongChem/posts/963307448490314">K Kwong@Facebook</a></p><p>K Kwong 表示，纸张本来就只应该用来印书写字，不应该用来制造餐具。K Kwong 称自己不会使用纸制餐具，因为造纸过程使用大量酸（H2SO4）、碱 (NaOH）、漂白剂 （Cl2，Cl2O，SO2）、萤光剂、防腐剂等，K Kwong 更指一张纸有过百种有害化学品，因此他自己不仅不使用纸餐具，甚至连用纸巾抹筷子、匙羹也不会。</p><p>K Kwong 另外又指纸张会吸水，倘若要用作制作餐具之原材料就必须加上防水涂层，纸包饮品涂层有塑胶、铝；纸餐具除了防水更要防油，所以或会加入含有 PFAS 的 Teflon，而纸餐具吸水后会变软，如是者又要加入填充物。K Kwong 指，现行法律并未规管填充物，因此厂商会选用非食用级的材质，如 CaCO3、TiO2。</p><div class="x11i5rnm xat24cr x1mh8g0r x1vvkbs xtlvy1s x126k92a"><div dir="auto"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1231238" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/20240425135530-694x416.jpg" alt="" width="694" height="416" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/20240425135530-694x416.jpg 694w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/20240425135530.jpg 705w" sizes="(max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 694px" /></div></div><p>资料来源： <a href="https://www.facebook.com/DrKKwongChem/posts/963307448490314">K Kwong@Facebook</a></p><br /><b>相关文章:</b><blockquote><li><a href="https://unwire.hk/2024/04/25/bamboo-knife-cut-steak-broke-twice/life-tech/green-2/?utm_source=inter&utm_medium=related&utm_campaign=rp" target="_blank">【走塑】供应商示范竹刀叉锯扒但两度截断，负责人：市民需时间适应</a></li>&nbsp;<li><a href="https://unwire.hk/2024/04/23/john-lee-said-no-plastic-doesnot-affect-citizen/life-tech/green-2/?utm_source=inter&utm_medium=related&utm_campaign=rp" target="_blank">李家超：「走塑」对市民影响不大，谢展寰：如替代餐具不耐用可试其他产品</a></li>&nbsp;<li><a href="https://unwire.hk/2024/04/23/netizen-sell-disposable-spoon-3000-hkd/life-tech/green-2/?utm_source=inter&utm_medium=related&utm_campaign=rp" target="_blank">网民售卖快餐店绝版塑胶餐具，标价 HK$3,000 不议价送纸巾</a></li>&nbsp;</blockquote><br /><p>The post <a href="https://unwire.hk/2024/04/25/paper-is-dirty-said-by-k-kwong/life-tech/green-2/">K Kwong：我唔想食纸   「纸餐具多有害化学物质、比想像污糟」</a> appeared first on <a href="https://unwire.hk">UNWIRE.HK</a>.</p>
]]>
            </description>
